can you get hepatitis c from sharing earrings with someone who doesnt have any disease no it is transmitted by blood to blood contact from an infected person's blood to a non infected person's blood the problem with hep c is that people often have it for years or even decades before they are diagnosed because they don't have any symptoms so the only way to be sure someone doesn't have hep c is if they've been tested recently treat other people's bodily fluids and blood as though they have a disease and you won't become infected in other words use gloves protection otherwise you're taking a chance best wishes Sexually-transmitted infection Hepatitis C Cytomegalovirus Prostate cancer Pneumonia Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Hepatitis B Blood Malaria Cirrhosis Ebola Hepatitis Diabetes mellitus Transmission (medicine) Infectious mononucleosis Common cold Traumatic brain injury HIV test Urinary incontinence Leptospirosis Multiple sclerosis Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Sickle-cell disease AIDS Marburg virus Tuberculosis Lassa fever Stomach cancer Cancer HIV Group A streptococcal infection Tattoo Medicine Infectious disease Duesberg hypothesis Safe sex Lyme disease Influenza Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease Balance disorder Blood transfusion Coeliac disease Sleeping sickness Stroke AIDS reappraisal Chronic fatigue syndrome Body fluid Syphilis Psoriasis Rabies West Nile virus Oral sex Rocky Mountain spotted fever Escherichia coli O157:H7 Hearing impairment Diabetic retinopathy Autism Paget's disease of bone Chagas disease Hyperglycemia Diagnosis Foodborne illness HIV Disease Progression Rates Crohn's disease Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Bleeding Anal sex Turner syndrome Dialysis Lupus erythematosus Body piercing Pelvic inflammatory disease Dysentery Gout Folic acid Lumbar puncture Kaposi's sarcoma Virus Alzheimer's disease Eczema Condom Gonorrhoea Disease Erectile dysfunction Organ transplant Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Emphysema Wilson's